          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Expanding Financial Access for Underserved Communities Act</strong></p> <p>This bill eases credit union membership requirements to allow more access for persons in underserved areas. A credit union must, however, submit a business and marketing plan to the National Credit Union Administration explaining the credit union's ability and intent to serve such population. </p> <p>The bill also excludes loans made to members in underserved areas from certain credit union limits on member business loans. </p>]]>
